{"TopicId":102558,"ForumId":36,"TopicTitle":"[1.0.5] LightsOut (v0.1.5) - Day/Night Mode in VAB/SPH","CreatedByName":"nodrog6","CreatedById":93747,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-03-23T23:05:53Z","PageNum":6,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"RealGecko","CreatedById":162682,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-11T08:54:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve published version 0.2.2, it\u0027s just a recompile for KSP 1.3.1, no other changes done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"agrock","CreatedById":182774,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-13T04:22:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLatest version does not work with KSP 1.3 (no menu in hangars).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso this version 0.2.2 that you mention, its not downloadable from either site.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aelfhe1m","CreatedById":142910,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-13T04:44:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223218060\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221510546963\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182774\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022agrock\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, agrock said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLatest version does not work with KSP 1.3 (no menu in hangars).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso this version 0.2.2 that you mention, its not downloadable from either site.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou need the RealGecko versions not the ones in the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://spacedock.info/mod/1006/Lights%20Out\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://spacedock.info/mod/1006/Lights Out\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0or\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/releases\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"agrock","CreatedById":182774,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-15T03:23:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you, LightsOut indeed works with KSP 1.3. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-26T09:49:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162682\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealGecko\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot sure if this is intended or not, but for some reason, the ambient light in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E don\u0027t dim quit enough, the light on craft goes on but the ambient light is not dark enough to show the real meaning of this mod, to check the lights in darkness !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealGecko","CreatedById":162682,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-03T07:47:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, I noticed that too, but I was only recompiling the mod to make sure it\u0027s compatible with latest KSP. Anyway I wont fix it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6881203523\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169185-leaving-community-dropping-mod-support/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:210px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo better luck with next maintainer.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealGecko","CreatedById":162682,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-17T04:25:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyone willing to take over? \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6804560168\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/169185-leaving-community-dropping-mod-support/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:212px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-21T13:51:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003Ehmm, i\u0027m not that familiar with ksp\u0027s api but i can take a look into this and see if i can figure what is going on or not\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, looking at the original repo, looks like there are tons of hard coded light names, shader names, etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know how to look for those names or even check if they exist or not, also, I\u0027m not sure if the way he is handling it is right way to go for this or not, honestly, if it was possible, maybe a better approach would be to turn off everything first then find lights on the ship and turn them back on, same for shaders, as i said, I\u0027m not that familiar with KSP some one like \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E would be a better person to take care of this although in linux\u0027s case, he already have tons on his plate\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-01-28T10:48:37Z\u0022 title=\u002201/28/2018 10:48  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 28, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Jiraiyah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"linuxgurugamer","CreatedById":129964,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-28T11:56:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked at this, but it\u2019s dealing with things I don\u2019t know Bout. \u00A0Best to find somebody else for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-10T16:14:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223279721\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517140619\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129964\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022linuxgurugamer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/28/2018 at 11:56 AM, linuxgurugamer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI looked at this, but it\u2019s dealing with things I don\u2019t know Bout. \u00A0Best to find somebody else for this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nouch, you where my only hope lol, not knowing many capable modders \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZobrAA","CreatedById":65233,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-22T09:55:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ELightsOut v0.2.2\u003C/a\u003E from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162682\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealGecko\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0still works fine.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jiraiyah","CreatedById":97667,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-09T11:28:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223330901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521712543\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002265233\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ZobrAA\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/22/2018 at 9:55 AM, ZobrAA said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ELightsOut v0.2.2\u003C/a\u003E from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162682\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealGecko\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0still works fine.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhonestly, i looked at the repo, but can\u0027t figure what is not working\u00A0 properly from his version\u00A0 that causes the lights to not be pitch dark like how it was supposed to be in older versions. any one has any idea?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhonestly, this line should have done it properly :\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LOAmbient.cs#L121\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LOAmbient.cs#L121\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat line is setting the ambient light to 0.15 on all RGB,\u00A0 unless, they have added more lights to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E than what is listed here, that would explain turning off a light would not turn\u00A0 the whole place dark\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LOExternalLights.cs#L38\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LOExternalLights.cs#L38\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbecause as you\u00A0 can see here, if it\u0027s night mode, it will disable the light, unless again, those conditions that were checked have any problems because of updates\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LOExternalLights.cs#L184\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LOExternalLights.cs#L184\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthis last method is being called from the main stuff in this line\u00A0 :\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LightsOut.cs#L131\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/blob/master/LightsOut/LightsOut.cs#L131\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nlong story short, does anyone know how we can check the name and number of lights in the scene and does anyone see any problem in the logic?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-04-09T11:41:04Z\u0022 title=\u002204/09/2018 11:41  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EApril 9, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Jiraiyah\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-04-24T21:21:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223330901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022102558\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221521712543\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002265233\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ZobrAA\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/22/2018 at 2:55 AM, ZobrAA said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks like\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/Real-Gecko/LightsOut/releases\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ELightsOut v0.2.2\u003C/a\u003E from \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022162682\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/162682-realgecko/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@RealGecko\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0still works fine.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSometimes \u0022good enough\u0022 is fine -- but ultimately it\u0027s probably a good idea to \u0022do it right\u0022 as Jiraiyah has noticed. Even not total blackness still gives a good idea of light placement, visiblity, etc. I\u0027ll likely be adding the mod back to my list if it fires up in 1.4.2 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Drew Kerman","CreatedById":103177,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-08-09T15:18:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeems to work just fine under KSP v1.4.5 w/MH\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraktal","CreatedById":184990,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-09-27T13:56:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYep, it does. I just wish I knew how to disable the damn hotkey.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}